## What I Learned

This problem taught me that I don't always need to compare every character manually.

My first thought was to compare each character of every string one by one, but that would make the solution longer and harder to understand. Instead, I learned that I can simply assume the first string is the common prefix and keep reducing it until every string starts with it.

Using built-in string functions like `find()` and `pop_back()` made the solution much cleaner and easier to implement.

